WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
[6 Months Ago]

00:00:37.020 --> 00:00:41.620
[Ichika Kogo]

00:00:54.250 --> 00:00:56.010
Are you dead?

00:01:00.550 --> 00:01:02.700
Gido?

00:01:02.700 --> 00:01:05.400
- Gido?
- Did you hope I'd be?

00:01:05.400 --> 00:01:07.240
[Ayumi Gido]

00:01:36.830 --> 00:01:38.880
Watch the rear.

00:01:42.280 --> 00:01:44.030
I've had it.

00:01:45.140 --> 00:01:52.690
I'm rebooting. Pull a fast one on me,
and your sister's dead.

00:01:54.850 --> 00:01:58.020
Or would you rather just kill me now?

00:02:04.630 --> 00:02:06.090
Go on.

00:02:07.240 --> 00:02:10.410
And make myself the prime suspect? No, thank you.

00:02:10.410 --> 00:02:12.550
Smart move.

00:02:12.550 --> 00:02:15.180
I knew you were a bright gal, Ichika.

00:02:18.850 --> 00:02:20.840
Stew these birds for me, will you?

00:02:20.840 --> 00:02:22.700
They nearly pecked me to death.

00:02:22.700 --> 00:02:24.390
Do it yourself.

00:02:24.390 --> 00:02:27.290
You know I'm a terrible cook.

00:02:27.290 --> 00:02:30.400
Come on, aren't I your sweetheart?

00:02:31.600 --> 00:02:34.700
[Present Day]

00:02:39.450 --> 00:02:41.580
Thank you, come again.
[Hayase Patisserie]

00:02:46.320 --> 00:02:50.680
[Riku Hayase]

00:02:57.370 --> 00:03:00.660
[Happy Birthday Mom!]

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:06.910
- How does that look?
- Perfect.

00:03:06.910 --> 00:03:08.440
- Great.
- Thank you for your patronage.

00:03:08.440 --> 00:03:10.280
Thanks for always dropping by, Mizuki.
[Takumi Hayase]

00:03:10.280 --> 00:03:12.480
Sure. Mom loves the cakes here, after all.

00:03:12.480 --> 00:03:16.710
- Mrs. Hinako's turning... 38 this year?
- Yup.

00:03:16.710 --> 00:03:18.780
- Okay.
- You have a great memory.

00:03:18.780 --> 00:03:20.650
Here's your cake.

00:03:20.650 --> 00:03:23.380
- Thank you.
- Give our regards to your mother.

00:03:35.300 --> 00:03:37.960
We can... fix that.

00:03:37.960 --> 00:03:40.020
Takumi, grab me four pieces
of Hayase Shortcakes.

00:03:40.020 --> 00:03:41.280
On it.
[Hayase Shortcakes]

00:03:57.360 --> 00:04:00.430
There you go.

00:04:03.600 --> 00:04:08.410
- But the money...
- Don't sweat it, these were leftovers. Right?

00:04:08.410 --> 00:04:11.000
Yup. The usual leftovers.

00:04:15.160 --> 00:04:16.470
- Thanks.
- Anytime.

00:04:16.470 --> 00:04:17.880
- Come again.
- Bye bye.

00:04:17.880 --> 00:04:20.540
- And be careful, alright?
- I will!

00:04:22.180 --> 00:04:24.960
- Nice work, Dad.
- Just don't tell your grandma.

00:04:26.440 --> 00:04:32.490
This is a business. You need the money!
[Ryoko Hayase]

00:04:32.490 --> 00:04:35.640
Mom, not when Takumi's around.

00:04:35.640 --> 00:04:40.130
Expenses are only rising,
yet you keep the same price.

00:04:40.130 --> 00:04:43.800
We're barely making a profit as is!

00:04:43.800 --> 00:04:46.420
I only hope you'll make
the business prosper, Takumi.

00:04:46.420 --> 00:04:49.440
Sorry, but I'm becoming a Youtuber.

00:04:49.440 --> 00:04:51.920
Then spread our name with your videos!

00:04:51.920 --> 00:04:55.520
I want us to become big,
like Cozy Corner and Fujiya.

00:04:55.520 --> 00:04:59.180
Unlike your selfless father here.

00:04:59.180 --> 00:05:00.910
Now get studying, alright?

00:05:00.910 --> 00:05:02.990
You've got your smarts from your mother,

00:05:02.990 --> 00:05:06.420
so go on and major in finance for us.

00:05:17.520 --> 00:05:19.810
- Hello there.
- Welcome.

00:05:22.510 --> 00:05:25.520
Huh, not bad.

00:05:25.520 --> 00:05:28.100
I like the no-frills aesthetic here.

00:05:28.100 --> 00:05:30.490
Thank you, sir.

00:05:30.490 --> 00:05:32.830
I think I'll get a cream puff.

00:05:32.830 --> 00:05:34.860
- You two want one?
- I'd appreciate it, sir.

00:05:34.860 --> 00:05:37.170
I think I'll pass.

00:05:37.170 --> 00:05:39.560
- Then we'll take two cream puffs.
- Sure thing.

00:05:46.620 --> 00:05:48.230
- You can skip the box.
- No, I insist.

00:05:48.230 --> 00:05:50.890
Don't bother, it'd only go in the trash.

00:05:50.890 --> 00:05:52.650
We're not getting these to-go.

00:05:53.450 --> 00:05:55.680
- You sure?
- Yeah.

00:05:57.280 --> 00:05:59.080
- There.
- Thank you.

00:06:04.560 --> 00:06:06.250
It's a cute little thing, ain't it?

00:06:15.100 --> 00:06:17.950
Yeah, that's what I'd call a cream puff.

00:06:19.880 --> 00:06:21.440
Thank you, sir.

00:06:21.440 --> 00:06:23.750
- Say, I've been wondering.
- Yes?

00:06:23.750 --> 00:06:26.660
What happens to all your leftovers?
Do they get trashed?

00:06:26.660 --> 00:06:29.070
Most don't hold, so unfortunately, yes.

00:06:29.070 --> 00:06:31.550
How about sharing them with your family?

00:06:31.550 --> 00:06:33.890
I'm sure your wife'd appreciate that.

00:06:33.890 --> 00:06:35.890
Natsumi Hayase, right?

00:06:37.490 --> 00:06:40.010
She had a real sweet tooth, or so I hear.

00:06:47.120 --> 00:06:49.940
The name's Gido. Tokyo Metropolitan Police,
First Investigation Team.

00:06:49.940 --> 00:06:52.220
- Likewise, I'm Teramoto.
- Adachi.

00:06:52.220 --> 00:06:58.340
A week ago, we unearthed a skeleton
buried on Mount Okutama.

00:07:06.960 --> 00:07:13.820
The body's been buried for two years,
with a bullet through the ribs.

00:07:13.820 --> 00:07:18.460
We believe the individual was shot,
and abandoned on the mountain.

00:07:21.190 --> 00:07:22.570
Why are you telling me all this?

00:07:22.570 --> 00:07:25.860
While we were investigating the remains,

00:07:25.860 --> 00:07:28.540
we came across a small wallet.

00:07:28.540 --> 00:07:30.250
And in it...

00:07:32.350 --> 00:07:37.400
We found the license of a "Natsumi Hayase".

00:07:37.400 --> 00:07:39.460
That would be your wife, no?

00:07:40.800 --> 00:07:45.470
You filed a missing persons report
two and a half years ago.

00:07:45.470 --> 00:07:50.040
I'm sorry to say, but we believe the body
is that of your wife.

00:07:51.300 --> 00:07:54.870
- Impossible...
- Could you direct us to her dentist?

00:07:54.870 --> 00:07:57.380
We'd like to compare her teeth
with that of the body's.

00:07:57.380 --> 00:08:00.560
- A used hairbrush would be nice, too.
- Lies!

00:08:00.560 --> 00:08:02.660
Sir, calm down.

00:08:26.990 --> 00:08:29.080
It's okay.

00:08:29.080 --> 00:08:31.480
I'm sure your mother is alive.

00:08:31.980 --> 00:08:35.070
You can't give up now.

00:08:35.070 --> 00:08:39.200
Us Hayase's are known for being tenacious.

00:08:44.250 --> 00:08:48.720
This ring was found
on the body's left ring finger.

00:08:48.720 --> 00:08:52.570
We've brought the aforementioned wallet as well.

00:08:52.570 --> 00:08:54.760
Please confirm their contents with us.

00:10:06.110 --> 00:10:07.860
Thank you.

00:10:10.850 --> 00:10:12.990
Thank you.

00:10:12.990 --> 00:10:17.350
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

00:10:20.190 --> 00:10:24.980
Hey, those are my candles!

00:10:35.900 --> 00:10:40.240
Your father's cakes are the best in the world.

00:10:40.240 --> 00:10:43.070
I wouldn't say best in the world, Natsumi.

00:10:43.070 --> 00:10:46.070
Then maybe... the best in town?

00:10:46.070 --> 00:10:47.890
- Just in town?
- Right.

00:10:47.890 --> 00:10:50.170
At least call it the best in Japan.

00:10:50.170 --> 00:10:53.020
Happy Birthday, Mom.

00:10:58.050 --> 00:11:01.420
[Dear Mom...]

00:11:07.800 --> 00:11:10.850
I'm tearing up with joy.

00:11:28.430 --> 00:11:31.000
Forensics have gotten back to us.

00:11:31.000 --> 00:11:37.010
Her dental records and DNA
are a complete match.

00:11:37.010 --> 00:11:40.540
The body is that of Natsumi Hayase.

00:11:40.540 --> 00:11:42.470
My condolences, sir.

00:12:34.690 --> 00:12:36.650
Takumi, your mother...

00:12:38.520 --> 00:12:40.840
has gone to heaven.

00:12:40.840 --> 00:12:43.660
- No!
- Taku!

00:12:43.660 --> 00:12:47.610
Mom isn't dead. Right, Grandma?

00:12:47.610 --> 00:12:48.660
Taku...

00:12:48.660 --> 00:12:51.120
What happened to not giving up?

00:12:51.120 --> 00:12:53.190
Takumi.

00:12:53.190 --> 00:12:55.000
I'm sorry.

00:12:56.230 --> 00:12:59.610
I'm sorry.

00:13:02.450 --> 00:13:05.070
I'm sorry.

00:13:05.740 --> 00:13:07.470
I'm sorry.

00:13:10.240 --> 00:13:13.820
This is Chima, from Clearance Law Office, speaking.

00:13:13.820 --> 00:13:15.870
You've reached our hotline for debt help.

00:13:15.870 --> 00:13:18.170
How may we assist you?
[Flow of Conversation]

00:13:18.170 --> 00:13:21.180
Rikka, what say we grab
some barbecue tonight?

00:13:21.180 --> 00:13:24.430
- Barbecue?
- If meat's not your thing, how about sushi?

00:13:24.430 --> 00:13:27.860
- I'll take you somewhere fancy.
- Sorry sir, I'm capped out today.

00:13:27.860 --> 00:13:28.580
[Isamu Kaieda]

00:13:28.580 --> 00:13:30.020
"Capped out"?

00:13:30.020 --> 00:13:32.840
It means I'm busy. Sorry, sir.

00:13:32.840 --> 00:13:35.750
Fine, fine.
[Rikka]

00:13:41.450 --> 00:13:42.940
So, how about it?

00:13:43.650 --> 00:13:46.390
We've met our 100-case daily quota, sir.

00:13:46.390 --> 00:13:51.160
Hey, I'm not talking business.
I'm inviting you out to dinner.

00:13:52.140 --> 00:13:55.610
All the other girls were dying to go.

00:13:55.610 --> 00:13:57.580
Sorry sir, but I've got work to do.

00:13:57.580 --> 00:14:00.850
You're a tough cookie, Machi.

00:14:00.850 --> 00:14:03.240
So loyal to your boyfriend.
[Machi]

00:14:03.240 --> 00:14:05.970
Then I suppose the rumors are true, eh?

00:14:05.970 --> 00:14:08.050
You're Fuyuhashi's sweetheart?

00:14:08.050 --> 00:14:09.760
Fuyuhashi and I are family, sir.

00:14:09.760 --> 00:14:12.820
Then why not grab dinner with me?

00:14:13.530 --> 00:14:15.520
Hello there, team.

00:14:15.520 --> 00:14:17.720
It's time to get going, Mr. Kaieda.

00:14:17.720 --> 00:14:19.840
Already?

00:14:19.840 --> 00:14:22.040
Fine. Talk to you later, Machi.

00:14:25.560 --> 00:14:29.080
I really don't think you need to take action, sir.
[Naoto Kiriya]

00:14:29.080 --> 00:14:31.210
Bah, it'll serve as a smoke break.

00:14:31.210 --> 00:14:35.390
Besides, I've got a reputation to maintain.

00:14:35.390 --> 00:14:38.810
Sounds rough.

00:14:38.810 --> 00:14:40.690
Shut it.

00:14:44.170 --> 00:14:45.220
There.

00:14:45.220 --> 00:14:47.300
[Kou Fuyuhashi]

00:14:47.300 --> 00:14:51.200
Funeral garb makes you look like a male host.

00:14:51.200 --> 00:14:54.050
No male host wears a suit nowadays, sir.

00:14:54.050 --> 00:14:55.900
Is that so?

00:14:58.300 --> 00:15:02.040
I've heard the rumors, Mr. Kaieda.

00:15:02.040 --> 00:15:06.240
And I'd rather you leave my associates be.

00:15:06.240 --> 00:15:10.120
Is that what you and Machi gossip about?

00:15:11.950 --> 00:15:14.610
How terrifying.

00:15:14.610 --> 00:15:18.200
Haven't you learned to respect your elders?

00:15:18.200 --> 00:15:23.940
Haven't you learned
to go after women your own age?

00:15:25.050 --> 00:15:28.610
Says the guy exploiting youngsters for money.

00:15:28.610 --> 00:15:32.720
So what if you're a savior
to some homeless brats.

00:15:32.720 --> 00:15:35.040
We're the same breed, you and I.

00:15:35.660 --> 00:15:38.320
- Get driving.
- On it.

00:15:38.320 --> 00:15:41.360
[Funeral Service: Mrs. Natsumi Hayase]

00:16:05.030 --> 00:16:08.150
Sir, I'm sorry to interrupt,
but someone is requesting your presence.

00:16:15.520 --> 00:16:18.880
I offer my sincere condolences
to you and your family, Mr. Hayase.

00:16:18.880 --> 00:16:22.850
My name is Kaieda. I work as an attorney.

00:16:23.530 --> 00:16:29.410
I am currently a legal consultant
for the GooSix Corporation.

00:16:29.410 --> 00:16:32.060
I ran into your wife at times at the company.

00:16:32.060 --> 00:16:33.810
Is that so?

00:16:33.810 --> 00:16:36.900
I apologize, but I know very little
about my wife's work.

00:16:36.900 --> 00:16:39.280
She was an outstanding member of the team.

00:16:39.280 --> 00:16:42.010
It is truly a shame we lost her so suddenly.

00:16:43.640 --> 00:16:50.350
Mr. Hayase, if I may ask.
Did your wife entrust you with anything?

00:16:50.350 --> 00:16:53.050
No, she did not. Why?

00:16:53.050 --> 00:17:00.670
Truth be told, your wife was to return
a rather important document to us.

00:17:00.670 --> 00:17:03.450
I see.

00:17:04.220 --> 00:17:08.250
She never informed me of such a thing.

00:17:08.250 --> 00:17:15.580
If you happen to find anything,
could you please contact my firm?

00:17:15.580 --> 00:17:17.010
I understand.

00:17:17.010 --> 00:17:20.780
Thank you for heeding my request
despite your mourning.

00:17:20.780 --> 00:17:22.860
Now if you'll excuse me.

00:17:33.940 --> 00:17:36.610
Our intel was on the mark.

00:17:36.610 --> 00:17:39.000
The culprit's Gido.

00:17:54.590 --> 00:17:57.040
What brings you here, Ms. Ichika?

00:18:00.000 --> 00:18:03.110
She was my predecessor.

00:18:03.110 --> 00:18:05.900
The least I can do is offer a prayer.

00:18:33.540 --> 00:18:36.830
You must be Takumi.

00:18:39.450 --> 00:18:43.930
My name is Ichika Kogo.
I worked alongside your mother.

00:18:44.810 --> 00:18:50.020
I also lost my parents when I was young.

00:18:50.850 --> 00:18:53.150
Here's a lesson I learned back then.

00:18:54.100 --> 00:18:59.390
No one comes to help someone looking down.

00:18:59.390 --> 00:19:03.940
I'm sure you must be hurting,
but you have to face the future yourself.

00:19:04.680 --> 00:19:06.400
You got this.

00:19:13.550 --> 00:19:15.580
Why did you talk to him?

00:19:15.580 --> 00:19:18.370
I wanted to help a mourning child.

00:19:18.370 --> 00:19:20.780
Any respectable adult would do the same.

00:19:22.340 --> 00:19:24.350
Is that Ichika I see?

00:19:24.980 --> 00:19:28.620
Mourning garb certainly suits you, my dear.

00:19:28.620 --> 00:19:33.590
Since Gido's going to kick the bucket,
how about jumping ship to me instead?

00:19:33.590 --> 00:19:35.670
Just name your price.

00:19:35.670 --> 00:19:38.000
100 million yen.

00:19:38.000 --> 00:19:41.250
What a pricey beauty indeed.

00:19:41.950 --> 00:19:44.670
[Dear customers,
we will be closing shop for a while]

00:19:50.120 --> 00:19:51.850
How's Takumi?

00:19:52.610 --> 00:19:54.590
He's still holed up in his room.

00:19:56.880 --> 00:19:59.890
He hasn't come to terms with it yet.

00:20:02.290 --> 00:20:05.040
Should I have let him see her after all?

00:20:06.220 --> 00:20:09.400
No, absolutely not.

00:20:09.400 --> 00:20:14.410
His mother ought to remain beautiful
in his heart.

00:20:17.190 --> 00:20:19.390
I have to pull myself together.

00:20:21.080 --> 00:20:24.010
I have to be the pillar for him.

00:20:39.960 --> 00:20:42.230
It's fine. I'll get it.

00:20:45.820 --> 00:20:48.540
My name is Mikami,
of the First Investigation Team.

00:20:48.540 --> 00:20:53.230
May we search your abode for leads
regarding Mrs. Natsumi Hayase?

00:20:56.940 --> 00:20:58.940
This was my wife's room.

00:20:58.940 --> 00:21:02.530
We haven't moved much since she went missing.

00:21:02.530 --> 00:21:04.490
May we borrow a couple of her items?

00:21:04.490 --> 00:21:07.210
We will return them to you
as soon as possible.

00:21:07.800 --> 00:21:09.020
Of course.

00:21:09.020 --> 00:21:10.260
- Take her laptop.
- Yes, sir.

00:21:10.260 --> 00:21:11.770
Laptop acquired.

00:21:11.770 --> 00:21:14.370
We just need to grab her work files, right?

00:21:14.370 --> 00:21:16.010
I believe so.

00:21:21.550 --> 00:21:24.160
- Hey there.
- Hello.

00:21:28.860 --> 00:21:32.770
[Hayase Patisserie]

00:21:39.900 --> 00:21:44.070
Don't sneak up on me like that.
It's terrifying.

00:21:54.900 --> 00:21:58.400
Isn't that Mr. Gido?

00:21:58.400 --> 00:21:59.920
Who is that next to him?

00:21:59.920 --> 00:22:01.740
Forget you ever saw them, for your own sake.

00:22:01.740 --> 00:22:03.470
What? Why?

00:22:03.470 --> 00:22:08.190
There are some things you're better off not knowing.

00:22:08.190 --> 00:22:10.200
Excuse me, coming through.

00:22:13.980 --> 00:22:16.850
Connections are crucial to business.
Especially lateral ones.

00:22:16.850 --> 00:22:19.480
- Indeed.
- How do you feel about hierarchical relations?

00:22:19.480 --> 00:22:22.290
Equally as crucial.
[Wataru Goroku]

00:22:22.290 --> 00:22:25.160
- I'm thinking of this for our layout.
- Looks good.

00:22:25.160 --> 00:22:27.570
- Looks wonderful.
- Thank you.

00:22:27.570 --> 00:22:29.100
- I think this is great.
- You sure?

00:22:29.100 --> 00:22:33.140
- What do you think, sir?
- Maybe change this one thing here.

00:22:33.140 --> 00:22:35.880
Sorry I made you take a detour.

00:22:35.880 --> 00:22:37.670
It's no problem.

00:22:38.880 --> 00:22:41.010
Take a look at this.

00:22:43.910 --> 00:22:48.460
These premium ingredients are the result

00:22:48.460 --> 00:22:53.410
of building trust with my suppliers.

00:22:53.410 --> 00:22:56.400
The same principle applies to any market.

00:22:56.400 --> 00:22:59.870
Business is all about building trust.

00:22:59.870 --> 00:23:03.910
And although trust is only built with time,

00:23:03.910 --> 00:23:07.420
it can easily be lost in an instant.

00:23:07.420 --> 00:23:11.420
Never to be regained again.

00:23:14.020 --> 00:23:16.460
Do you understand what I'm getting at?

00:23:18.280 --> 00:23:19.800
Yes, sir.

00:23:21.710 --> 00:23:24.000
Hurry up and find it.

00:23:25.220 --> 00:23:27.080
I'm counting on you.

00:23:43.020 --> 00:23:45.270
What're you doing?

00:23:45.270 --> 00:23:47.080
Takumi...

00:23:48.080 --> 00:23:52.350
I'm making your mom's favorite,
a Hayase Shortcake.

00:24:03.660 --> 00:24:05.880
Teach me.

00:24:07.260 --> 00:24:11.130
I want to make a Hayase Shortcake, too.

00:24:15.540 --> 00:24:18.370
Sure. But take off your cardigan first.

00:24:20.170 --> 00:24:22.860
- Careful, don't spill.
- Alright.

00:24:24.550 --> 00:24:26.110
Watch out.

00:24:28.170 --> 00:24:30.080
- Looks good.
- Yeah.

00:24:35.560 --> 00:24:37.480
Make sure you get the edges.

00:24:39.020 --> 00:24:42.370
Or we can call it a unique design.

00:24:49.180 --> 00:24:51.000
- You're good.
- Yeah?

00:24:51.530 --> 00:24:53.270
Try copying me.

00:24:56.250 --> 00:24:57.690
Looking good.

00:24:57.690 --> 00:24:59.240
You got it.

00:25:07.800 --> 00:25:09.550
Done.

00:25:10.670 --> 00:25:15.130
Pretty good for your first try, champ.

00:25:16.120 --> 00:25:18.610
That looks amazing, Taku!

00:25:18.610 --> 00:25:23.150
- Right?
- Yes, it looks delicious.

00:25:24.090 --> 00:25:27.570
Takumi made his very first Hayase Shortcake.

00:25:27.570 --> 00:25:29.220
Give it a try.

00:25:30.820 --> 00:25:35.020
Dad. I want to take over the family business.

00:25:35.020 --> 00:25:36.200
What?

00:25:36.200 --> 00:25:40.660
I want to keep Mom's favorite cake alive.

00:25:57.020 --> 00:25:58.820
Natsumi.

00:25:59.910 --> 00:26:04.250
I'll raise Takumi into a fine lad.

00:26:04.250 --> 00:26:10.050
We'll be happy, for your sake.

00:26:12.420 --> 00:26:15.630
Though we have confirmed
a withdrawal of money,

00:26:15.630 --> 00:26:19.120
it is likely unrelated to this case.
[Investigation of the Mt. Okutama Murder]

00:26:19.120 --> 00:26:22.960
Next, we would like to discuss
the contents of Natsumi Hayase's laptop.

00:26:22.960 --> 00:26:26.440
Our tech team discovered...

00:26:26.440 --> 00:26:29.190
this rather concerning text file.

00:26:40.390 --> 00:26:43.710
Good afternoon, Inspector Gido.

00:26:45.740 --> 00:26:47.460
Hey there, sir.

00:26:47.460 --> 00:26:52.010
Come on, don't be so cold.
I'm no grim reaper.

00:26:52.010 --> 00:26:55.040
Well, I'd rather not draw unneeded attention,

00:26:55.040 --> 00:26:56.970
especially where folks are watching.

00:26:56.970 --> 00:27:00.380
I only want to chat, that's all.

00:27:00.380 --> 00:27:04.100
I heard you volunteered

00:27:04.100 --> 00:27:06.630
to investigate this case yourself.

00:27:06.630 --> 00:27:08.000
That, I did.

00:27:08.740 --> 00:27:12.410
I wouldn't call this case
especially riveting.

00:27:13.520 --> 00:27:16.190
What inspired you to take such quick action?

00:27:17.650 --> 00:27:21.990
I'm only performing my duties as an officer.

00:27:26.570 --> 00:27:28.870
What a model police officer you are.

00:27:28.870 --> 00:27:31.360
I appreciate the compliment, sir.
Good day.

00:27:33.780 --> 00:27:38.810
[Masachika Makita]

00:27:38.810 --> 00:27:42.830
It almost seems like you all are accusing me.

00:27:42.830 --> 00:27:47.120
We investigated the financial history
behind Hayase Patisserie.

00:27:47.120 --> 00:27:52.920
Your store barely made profit,
and your wife's earnings

00:27:52.920 --> 00:27:56.140
supported both the family and store, correct?

00:27:56.140 --> 00:27:57.120
Yes, that is correct.

00:27:57.120 --> 00:28:02.700
So you were jealous of your money-making wife.

00:28:02.700 --> 00:28:05.750
No, never. What is this all about?

00:28:05.750 --> 00:28:09.550
Did you know your wife kept a diary
on her laptop?

00:28:09.550 --> 00:28:10.890
A diary?

00:28:10.890 --> 00:28:16.230
She recounts your physical abuse
caused by this financial imbalance.

00:28:16.230 --> 00:28:17.450
Pardon?

00:28:17.450 --> 00:28:22.130
In her final entry, she even confessed
how you could very well "kill her".

00:28:22.130 --> 00:28:24.010
W-Wait, I didn't -

00:28:24.010 --> 00:28:29.760
You were on route to the scene of her murder

00:28:29.760 --> 00:28:35.980
on March 14th, the day she was murdered.

00:28:35.980 --> 00:28:38.860
I was taking a dessert-eating road trip.

00:28:38.860 --> 00:28:41.240
Then you made a detour to bury the body.

00:28:41.240 --> 00:28:43.000
I would never.

00:28:43.000 --> 00:28:46.140
Now, now. Calm down, sir.

00:28:46.140 --> 00:28:48.920
For now, please tell us all the stores
you visited that day.

00:28:48.920 --> 00:28:53.560
We will also investigate your car,
and track your credit card usage.

00:28:53.560 --> 00:28:55.300
Understood?

00:28:55.300 --> 00:28:56.870
Yes, sir.

00:29:21.240 --> 00:29:24.000
[Unidentified Number]

00:29:28.220 --> 00:29:29.550
Hello?

00:29:29.550 --> 00:29:32.920
This is Gido, from the investigation team.

00:29:33.650 --> 00:29:37.380
- Good evening.
- We found blood on your car, Mr. Hayase.

00:29:37.380 --> 00:29:41.650
- What?
- And forensics say it's Mrs. Natsumi's.

00:29:41.650 --> 00:29:44.170
- Why?
- You're being filed with an arrest warrant.

00:29:44.170 --> 00:29:47.610
This has to be a mistake. I'm innocent!

00:29:47.610 --> 00:29:49.870
I know.

00:29:49.870 --> 00:29:52.750
You're being framed.

00:29:52.750 --> 00:29:55.000
- What?
- I'll make you a deal.

00:29:55.000 --> 00:29:58.940
Work with me, and let's avenge Natsumi.

00:30:00.590 --> 00:30:01.870
What are you talking about?

00:30:01.870 --> 00:30:05.700
I'm saying we share an enemy here.

00:30:05.700 --> 00:30:08.800
You know more about Natsumi's death?

00:30:08.800 --> 00:30:10.540
Let's talk about the details in person.

00:30:10.540 --> 00:30:12.420
Leave your house, now.

00:30:12.420 --> 00:30:13.700
Where should I go?

00:30:13.700 --> 00:30:15.580
Your place is already surrounded.

00:30:15.580 --> 00:30:18.620
Escape out the second floor,
and only carry cash on you.

00:30:18.620 --> 00:30:20.500
Hold on, I'm not following.

00:30:20.500 --> 00:30:22.620
- I'll call you back later.
- What?

00:30:24.940 --> 00:30:29.240
[Hayase Patisserie]

00:30:33.740 --> 00:30:38.440
Good evening, ma'am.
We're here to arrest Riku Hayase.

00:30:38.440 --> 00:30:40.190
- What?
- Excuse us.

00:30:40.190 --> 00:30:42.500
- Please, wait.
- Sorry, ma'am.

00:30:42.500 --> 00:30:44.690
What is going on?

00:31:37.170 --> 00:31:39.580
Gido?

00:31:39.580 --> 00:31:43.380
Gido? This is Hayase.

00:31:43.380 --> 00:31:44.980
Gido?

00:31:54.370 --> 00:31:56.060
Gido?

00:32:03.500 --> 00:32:05.760
G-Gido!

00:32:05.760 --> 00:32:08.450
Get a grip, Gido!

00:32:08.450 --> 00:32:11.220
I'll call an ambulance right away.

00:32:14.460 --> 00:32:18.170
Take that car and go to my apartment.

00:32:18.170 --> 00:32:21.440
- I live in room 608.
- B-But!

00:32:22.150 --> 00:32:25.920
Stay here, and you'll be framed
for my murder, too.

00:32:25.920 --> 00:32:27.460
What?

00:32:27.460 --> 00:32:29.840
There's an enemy within the police.

00:32:29.840 --> 00:32:30.990
Sorry?

00:32:30.990 --> 00:32:34.110
If they catch you, it's over.

00:32:35.300 --> 00:32:37.770
Who's behind all this?

00:32:37.770 --> 00:32:42.830
Just... grab the file at my place.

00:32:44.120 --> 00:32:46.200
Gido? Gido!

00:32:46.200 --> 00:32:49.460
Gido! Hey, Gido!

00:32:52.150 --> 00:32:53.950
Gido?

00:34:46.180 --> 00:34:47.800
N-No, I...

00:34:49.040 --> 00:34:51.100
You must be Riku Hayase.

00:34:52.670 --> 00:34:54.090
How did you...

00:35:00.200 --> 00:35:02.790
[Riku Hayase, Wanted Man]

00:35:02.790 --> 00:35:05.250
No, I'm innocent.

00:35:05.250 --> 00:35:07.810
Gido told me to come here.

00:35:07.810 --> 00:35:11.240
He said I was being framed.

00:35:12.230 --> 00:35:14.890
I came looking for a file,

00:35:14.890 --> 00:35:16.410
but his place was already like this.

00:35:21.050 --> 00:35:22.640
What happened to Gido?

00:35:28.690 --> 00:35:30.990
He had been stabbed.

00:35:31.900 --> 00:35:33.640
He died?

00:35:38.460 --> 00:35:43.020
I'll go to the police and confess everything.

00:35:44.330 --> 00:35:46.870
You're being set up.

00:35:46.870 --> 00:35:48.590
There's an enemy within the police.

00:35:48.590 --> 00:35:52.580
If you turn yourself in, you'll be framed
for both your wife and Gido's deaths.

00:35:52.580 --> 00:35:54.970
I'm sure they'll understand if I explain.

00:35:54.970 --> 00:35:58.830
Don't you realize the danger you're in?

00:36:06.360 --> 00:36:09.350
[GooSix Co. - Ichika Kogo]

00:36:09.350 --> 00:36:12.080
This is where Natsumi worked.

00:36:12.080 --> 00:36:13.710
You know my wife?

00:36:13.710 --> 00:36:17.900
I've never met her,
but I do know what she was up to.

00:36:17.900 --> 00:36:20.900
We were given the same task, after all.

00:36:20.900 --> 00:36:23.090
Task?

00:36:23.090 --> 00:36:26.910
To assist in money laundering.

00:36:29.670 --> 00:36:30.770
[Goosix Co.]

00:36:30.770 --> 00:36:35.520
Goroku runs an honest business upfront.

00:36:35.520 --> 00:36:38.490
But on the flip side,
he controls the flow of dirty money.

00:36:38.490 --> 00:36:41.890
Though he mainly handles
foreign online casino earnings,

00:36:41.890 --> 00:36:46.600
he deals with tainted capital
from all walks of life.

00:36:46.600 --> 00:36:51.290
To those involved in shady business,
he's known as the "Dark Banker".

00:36:52.100 --> 00:36:54.660
My job is to manage all of those funds.

00:36:54.660 --> 00:36:56.450
As was Natsumi's.

00:36:56.450 --> 00:36:58.300
No, Natsumi would never.

00:36:58.300 --> 00:37:01.340
If you don't believe me,
go see the truth for yourself.

00:37:02.220 --> 00:37:05.790
But you face an influential opponent.

00:37:05.790 --> 00:37:10.400
Turn yourself in,
and you'll be punished with death.

00:37:10.400 --> 00:37:12.030
Death...

00:37:15.840 --> 00:37:18.860
You'll be leaving your only child behind.

00:37:21.530 --> 00:37:25.000
What should I...

00:37:26.660 --> 00:37:28.380
You must reboot.

00:37:28.990 --> 00:37:31.300
"Reboot"?

00:37:31.300 --> 00:37:36.520
Change your face, and take on a new name.

00:37:36.520 --> 00:37:39.530
That's impossible.

00:37:39.530 --> 00:37:43.400
It's a method of survival
for those who live seedy lives.

00:37:43.400 --> 00:37:47.590
I'll introduce you to a surgeon
who can transform you into him.

00:37:47.590 --> 00:37:49.030
Into who?

00:37:49.030 --> 00:37:50.450
Gido.

00:37:51.170 --> 00:37:53.920
I can make it happen.

00:37:53.920 --> 00:37:56.010
Hold on a second.

00:37:56.010 --> 00:37:59.810
Gido was investigating
Goroku's business undercover.

00:37:59.810 --> 00:38:04.400
Become Gido, and you'll have police intel,
and access to Goroku's circle.

00:38:05.100 --> 00:38:06.900
I could never.

00:38:06.900 --> 00:38:09.790
Well, you don't have a choice
if you want to survive.

00:38:11.970 --> 00:38:14.440
Why would you go so far to help me?

00:38:16.950 --> 00:38:20.200
Gido was my lover.

00:38:20.200 --> 00:38:25.460
He was trying to get me
out of Goroku's clutches.

00:38:26.890 --> 00:38:29.280
It's because I know how you feel.

00:38:29.280 --> 00:38:32.410
They murdered my special someone, too.

00:38:33.240 --> 00:38:37.660
So work with me to find the true culprit.

00:39:34.120 --> 00:39:35.840
Hot.

00:39:36.900 --> 00:39:38.280
Can't handle hot temps?

00:39:38.280 --> 00:39:39.670
No.

00:39:45.710 --> 00:39:47.440
So?

00:39:49.850 --> 00:39:51.840
That was certainly Gido.

00:39:53.950 --> 00:39:57.430
And you? Are you ready?

00:40:00.170 --> 00:40:02.520
There's one thing I want to do before I go.

00:40:04.260 --> 00:40:05.650
Taku, come on.

00:40:05.650 --> 00:40:09.000
- Where are you going?
- I'm allowing my grandson to rest.

00:40:10.640 --> 00:40:13.400
Neither of us have slept a wink.

00:40:13.400 --> 00:40:15.870
Please, give us some time alone.

00:40:23.270 --> 00:40:24.720
Have you managed to contact Gido?

00:40:24.720 --> 00:40:27.900
No, sir.

00:40:27.900 --> 00:40:30.910
What is he up to now?

00:40:36.820 --> 00:40:39.000
[Crawfish Fishing]

00:41:18.000 --> 00:41:20.440
- Where did you go?
- I'm sorry.

00:41:20.440 --> 00:41:24.950
I didn't kill your mother, okay?

00:41:24.950 --> 00:41:26.460
Of course you didn't.

00:41:26.460 --> 00:41:28.910
Go tell the police you're innocent!

00:41:28.910 --> 00:41:33.940
If I turn myself in now,
I won't ever see you again.

00:41:33.940 --> 00:41:36.900
I have to go find the culprit myself.

00:41:36.900 --> 00:41:41.570
Takumi, I'm sorry. But I have to go.

00:41:41.570 --> 00:41:42.690
Go where?

00:41:42.690 --> 00:41:44.420
I'm sorry, I can't tell you.

00:41:44.420 --> 00:41:47.920
I know it'll be rough for you and Grandma.

00:41:47.920 --> 00:41:51.250
But I promise I'll catch the culprit.

00:41:51.250 --> 00:41:53.840
No, don't go!

00:41:54.800 --> 00:41:56.810
I'm sorry, Takumi.

00:41:59.210 --> 00:42:02.220
I'm coming with you.

00:42:02.900 --> 00:42:04.750
Takumi.

00:42:05.710 --> 00:42:11.230
Hold down the fort while I'm gone, okay?

00:42:12.230 --> 00:42:16.950
I don't want to lose you too, Dad.

00:42:20.980 --> 00:42:23.050
I'm sorry.

00:42:23.050 --> 00:42:24.650
I'm sorry.

00:42:26.030 --> 00:42:28.880
I promise I'll come back home to you.

00:42:44.800 --> 00:42:47.680
The police are headed your way.

00:42:47.680 --> 00:42:50.980
- Run!
- Ma'am, please give us back the phone!

00:42:57.200 --> 00:43:00.140
He knows we're coming.

00:43:00.140 --> 00:43:01.980
Surround him, now!

00:43:07.720 --> 00:43:10.080
I love you.

00:43:10.080 --> 00:43:12.190
I promise I'll come back.

00:43:16.950 --> 00:43:19.730
Go, hurry!

00:43:21.770 --> 00:43:24.600
Riku Hayase is headed west!

00:43:31.460 --> 00:43:34.820
Dad! Run!

00:43:36.410 --> 00:43:38.480
Run!

00:43:39.740 --> 00:43:41.710
Run away!

00:43:53.690 --> 00:43:56.930
So? Have you finally made up your mind?

00:43:56.930 --> 00:43:59.380
I'll do anything.

00:43:59.380 --> 00:44:02.210
If it means I see my family again, anything.

00:44:34.950 --> 00:44:36.400
What are you doing?

00:44:36.400 --> 00:44:40.200
I'm taking his fingerprint.
We might need it.

00:45:01.420 --> 00:45:06.680
Sir, could I ask you for a favor?

00:45:06.680 --> 00:45:08.460
What's up?

00:45:09.750 --> 00:45:12.580
I'd like some time off, if possible.

00:45:12.580 --> 00:45:16.470
Time off? Now why's that?

00:45:19.910 --> 00:45:24.220
- Truth be told, I'm not feeling so well.
- I'll contact Gido's superior as "himself".

00:45:24.220 --> 00:45:27.990
- What? Are you sick?
- Technology makes this a possible feat.

00:45:27.990 --> 00:45:32.010
I was diagnosed with major depression, sir.

00:45:32.010 --> 00:45:33.730
I'll schedule Gido for an extended leave,

00:45:33.730 --> 00:45:37.570
under the guise of attending "therapy".

00:45:37.570 --> 00:45:39.450
Much appreciated, sir.

00:45:39.450 --> 00:45:45.270
First, we will need to contour your jawline.

00:45:45.270 --> 00:45:49.830
We'll remove a part of your jawbone.
[Hitomi Kuwahara]

00:45:49.830 --> 00:45:51.610
Next to consider would be your neck.

00:45:51.610 --> 00:45:55.790
We will surgically change your vocal chords.

00:45:55.790 --> 00:45:57.650
You'll need half a year to recover.

00:45:57.650 --> 00:46:03.820
I will remotely report to Gido's superiors
as necessary.

00:46:04.590 --> 00:46:10.080
In the meantime, you will need to study up
on Gido's life and interpersonal relations.

00:46:19.930 --> 00:46:23.100
This individual is Gido's wife,
Mayu Gido.

00:46:23.100 --> 00:46:25.440
No talking.

00:46:25.440 --> 00:46:29.280
They've been living apart for years.
You won't be seeing her around.

00:46:31.900 --> 00:46:35.400
Once your throat is ready,
start practicing Gido's speech patterns.

00:46:35.400 --> 00:46:39.870
Gido here. Give me any updates on the deal.

00:46:41.330 --> 00:46:45.450
Gido here. Give me any updates on the deal.

00:46:49.070 --> 00:46:53.040
Make sure to perfect his handwriting.
Especially how he writes his name.

00:47:27.200 --> 00:47:31.370
You'll also need to train as an officer,
and learn how to use a firearm.

00:47:33.780 --> 00:47:36.550
Acquiring a gun is easy for Goroku's people.

00:47:52.130 --> 00:47:56.340
[Ayumi Gido, Reboot - Day 1]

00:48:07.700 --> 00:48:09.950
Perfect.

00:48:10.560 --> 00:48:16.100
You may feel strange at first,
but you'll settle in in due time.

00:48:22.040 --> 00:48:24.010
Then if you'll excuse me.

00:48:30.690 --> 00:48:34.040
Here's your new phone.

00:48:36.660 --> 00:48:41.140
You'll also need Gido's watch, and necklace.

00:48:50.350 --> 00:48:53.980
Don't forget to remove your ring.

00:49:40.420 --> 00:49:41.730
Thank you again.
[Hayase Patisserie]

00:49:41.730 --> 00:49:46.360
Of course. I love the cream puffs here.

00:49:46.360 --> 00:49:49.880
That makes me so happy to hear.

00:49:52.880 --> 00:49:55.960
Are you feeling alright, ma'am?

00:49:57.450 --> 00:50:00.770
Oh, I just fell from some stairs.

00:50:00.770 --> 00:50:02.960
Otherwise, I've never felt better!

00:50:11.840 --> 00:50:12.880
How was she?

00:50:12.880 --> 00:50:15.360
Cream puffs are about all she can make.

00:50:15.360 --> 00:50:18.720
But your son has been attending school.

00:50:18.720 --> 00:50:22.630
Thank you for always checking up on them.

00:50:22.630 --> 00:50:25.260
I've practically become a regular there.

00:50:26.080 --> 00:50:28.850
- Here.
- Wasn't I on a diet?

00:50:28.850 --> 00:50:31.050
I won't be controlling your life anymore.

00:50:31.050 --> 00:50:35.600
But Gido doesn't have a sweet tooth,
so no indulging in public, alright?

00:50:50.220 --> 00:50:51.650
How is it?

00:50:54.880 --> 00:50:57.130
It tastes like earnest effort.

00:50:59.830 --> 00:51:02.030
Pull yourself together, alright?

00:51:02.030 --> 00:51:04.790
Gido was never the sentimental type.

00:51:04.790 --> 00:51:06.340
Right, sorry.

00:51:07.350 --> 00:51:10.550
You are now Ayumi Gido.

00:51:10.550 --> 00:51:16.460
No matter what hardships come your way,
you must never drop your act.

00:51:17.980 --> 00:51:19.350
Yes, ma'am.

00:51:33.630 --> 00:51:38.090
Sorry, I was just surprised to see you smile.

00:51:39.250 --> 00:51:43.640
Desserts help me forget
the bad things in life.

00:51:54.860 --> 00:52:01.470
Once you take Gido's name,
his killer will surely come after you.

00:52:01.470 --> 00:52:04.010
There's an enemy within the police.

00:52:11.390 --> 00:52:14.280
Never let your guard down.

00:52:16.360 --> 00:52:18.910
Did you gain weight, Chief Mikami?

00:52:18.910 --> 00:52:22.170
Those cabaret clubs in Koenji
aren't doing you any favors.

00:52:22.170 --> 00:52:24.440
Better already?

00:52:24.440 --> 00:52:26.830
Thanks to the time off you gave me, sir.

00:52:26.830 --> 00:52:31.280
Here's a little something
for you and the missus.

00:52:31.280 --> 00:52:33.980
Never took you to be the considerate type.

00:52:33.980 --> 00:52:38.060
This is the least I can offer
after being away for half a year.

00:52:38.060 --> 00:52:40.050
Inspector Gido.

00:52:41.700 --> 00:52:43.150
Teramoto, Adachi.

00:52:43.150 --> 00:52:45.540
- Welcome back, sir.
- You've recovered already?

00:52:45.540 --> 00:52:47.430
Wanna get beers and see for yourself?

00:52:47.430 --> 00:52:50.820
Sir, I told you that sort of offer
is old school.

00:52:50.820 --> 00:52:55.030
I wouldn't mind joining you,
so long as we're off the clock.

00:52:55.030 --> 00:52:57.390
Fine. Tell me what leads I missed.

00:52:57.390 --> 00:52:59.510
"Leads"?

00:52:59.510 --> 00:53:04.730
Yeah... We were tailing Riku Hayase.

00:53:05.510 --> 00:53:07.350
I'm still handling the case, right?

00:53:07.350 --> 00:53:10.110
Sure.

00:53:10.110 --> 00:53:12.010
- We'll fill you in over there.
- Great.

00:53:14.410 --> 00:53:16.100
Wait.

00:53:19.220 --> 00:53:21.020
Am I busted?

00:53:25.120 --> 00:53:29.330
Remember, the lingerie club in Nakano
is our secret.

00:53:30.490 --> 00:53:33.300
Make fun of me for the Koenji pub,
but that's all I'll let slide.

00:53:33.300 --> 00:53:36.280
Yeah, yeah. Your secret's safe with me, boss.

00:53:41.580 --> 00:53:47.010
To be honest, the case has remained stagnant
for the past six months.

00:53:47.010 --> 00:53:51.180
Our best explanation is that Riku Hayase
was driven to suicide.

00:53:51.180 --> 00:53:54.500
Now we're the only ones working on this case.

00:53:54.500 --> 00:53:55.920
Sir, coffee?

00:53:55.920 --> 00:54:00.270
- Thanks.
- I appreciate the lack of overtime though.

00:54:01.630 --> 00:54:03.400
Was it too hot?

00:54:03.400 --> 00:54:07.680
Nah. So what're our other leads?

00:54:07.680 --> 00:54:09.480
Other leads?

00:54:09.480 --> 00:54:15.030
Who else are we suspecting
aside from Riku Hayase?

00:54:17.390 --> 00:54:19.370
Neither of you looked into it?

00:54:20.730 --> 00:54:24.560
Sir, he was filed an arrest warrant.
We were ordered to...

00:54:24.560 --> 00:54:27.700
Forget Riku Hayase for a second.
We gotta branch out.

00:54:27.700 --> 00:54:28.990
But sir...

00:54:28.990 --> 00:54:34.750
Look into Natsumi Hayase again.
I'm thinking we've got the wrong guy.

00:54:34.750 --> 00:54:36.620
Why is that?

00:54:39.490 --> 00:54:41.250
Why?

00:54:44.220 --> 00:54:48.550
Call it... a detective's hunch.

00:54:48.550 --> 00:54:50.220
I'll leave you two to it.

00:54:53.050 --> 00:54:57.990
Was Inspector Gido one to talk
about a "detective's hunch"?

00:54:57.990 --> 00:55:02.160
Maybe the break gave him an epiphany.

00:55:04.470 --> 00:55:06.170
This is so hard.

00:55:06.170 --> 00:55:08.380
Being an inspector is tough!

00:55:08.380 --> 00:55:10.750
I haven't been busted yet, right?

00:55:10.750 --> 00:55:12.870
God, I just want to make meringue.

00:55:12.870 --> 00:55:15.720
I miss baking cakes. I miss piping cream.

00:55:16.740 --> 00:55:21.030
At least I can investigate Natsumi's case.

00:55:21.030 --> 00:55:25.620
This gives me a chance
to find the true culprit.

00:55:26.640 --> 00:55:28.450
Inspector Gido!

00:55:28.450 --> 00:55:31.790
Congratulations on your recovery.

00:55:32.520 --> 00:55:34.280
Who is this?

00:55:34.280 --> 00:55:36.230
He wasn't listed in my documents.

00:55:36.230 --> 00:55:38.200
And you are?

00:55:38.950 --> 00:55:43.200
Sorry, but half a year away
makes the brain fuzzy.

00:55:46.400 --> 00:55:51.850
Well, I remember you well, Inspector Gido.

00:55:55.270 --> 00:55:56.440
[General Inspector: Masachika Makita]

00:55:56.440 --> 00:55:58.670
A General Inspector?

00:55:58.670 --> 00:56:02.570
That's someone who investigates
corrupt officers, right?

00:56:02.570 --> 00:56:06.690
Like the police of the police.

00:56:06.690 --> 00:56:10.290
Relax, I'm not here to interrogate you.

00:56:10.290 --> 00:56:12.480
Right.

00:56:12.480 --> 00:56:17.250
You never returned home
in the time you were gone. Why's that?

00:56:18.040 --> 00:56:20.770
I was recovering out in the countryside.

00:56:20.770 --> 00:56:25.500
Fuyuhashi and his men were looking for you.

00:56:25.500 --> 00:56:27.310
Fuyuhashi?

00:56:27.310 --> 00:56:31.050
This is Kou Fuyuhashi,
a direct subordinate of Goroku.

00:56:31.050 --> 00:56:37.980
He does all of Goroku's dirty work
from punishing traitors, to disposing bodies.

00:56:37.980 --> 00:56:40.020
He knew about Fuyuhashi?

00:56:40.020 --> 00:56:46.950
Then he must know about Gido
investigating Goroku undercover.

00:56:47.550 --> 00:56:51.850
Is that so? I had no idea.

00:56:52.580 --> 00:56:55.410
Then you'll admit you know Fuyuhashi?

00:56:56.360 --> 00:57:00.830
I was going undercover.
I was bound to run into him.

00:57:00.830 --> 00:57:04.410
Undercover investigations
aren't within your division's jurisdiction.

00:57:06.250 --> 00:57:11.640
Does this mean you were using Fuyuhashi
as your S?

00:57:11.640 --> 00:57:16.700
[S: Codeword for "informant"]

00:57:18.900 --> 00:57:21.020
Something like that.

00:57:21.840 --> 00:57:28.280
Were you not in hiding
because of trouble with Fuyuhashi's group?

00:57:28.280 --> 00:57:29.210
"Trouble"?

00:57:29.210 --> 00:57:35.020
You were selling him police intel,
were you not?

00:57:35.020 --> 00:57:37.180
Now hold on.

00:57:37.180 --> 00:57:40.280
Why would I ever do that?
I'm a fellow officer.

00:57:40.280 --> 00:57:43.070
Right, you would never do such a thing.

00:57:43.070 --> 00:57:47.030
Because that would be unthinkable,
for an officer.

00:57:47.030 --> 00:57:48.480
Go on, have a sip.

00:57:58.130 --> 00:58:01.810
Gido was under scrutiny
from the General Inspector?

00:58:01.810 --> 00:58:05.050
His files didn't mention that.

00:58:06.110 --> 00:58:07.750
So?

00:58:07.750 --> 00:58:13.040
He was clearly flustered,
but nothing he said was a lie.

00:58:27.280 --> 00:58:28.310
Welcome home.

00:58:28.310 --> 00:58:32.910
Ichika. Gido got interrogated today.

00:58:32.910 --> 00:58:36.380
We'll chat later. We have to head out, now.

00:58:36.380 --> 00:58:39.910
- What?
- Goroku's orders. Come on.

00:58:39.910 --> 00:58:42.850
- Now?
- Hurry.

00:58:42.850 --> 00:58:44.530
Oh man...

00:58:48.350 --> 00:58:50.080
Ayumi?

00:58:50.080 --> 00:58:51.870
Ayumi!

00:58:52.450 --> 00:58:55.420
Where have you been?
I've been looking for you!

00:58:56.050 --> 00:58:57.450
I'm sorry, but we're in a rush.

00:58:57.450 --> 00:58:59.050
Who is that?

00:58:59.670 --> 00:59:01.830
She's a colleague.

00:59:02.620 --> 00:59:05.200
Ayumi, if you ever need anything,
come talk to me.

00:59:05.200 --> 00:59:08.520
I thought Gido never spoke to his wife.

00:59:08.520 --> 00:59:13.000
I'll keep visiting until you'll talk.

00:59:13.000 --> 00:59:15.680
- Drive.
- Yes, ma'am.

00:59:21.440 --> 00:59:25.400
[Mayu Gido]

01:00:20.750 --> 01:00:26.070
A number of bigwigs partake
in money laundering within the org.

01:00:26.070 --> 01:00:32.890
And the one who holds the reigns,
is none other than Wataru Goroku.

01:00:33.710 --> 01:00:36.700
Long time no see, Gido.

01:00:36.700 --> 01:00:38.960
You too, Ichika.

01:00:38.960 --> 01:00:41.440
I'm sure you must be fired up.

01:00:41.440 --> 01:00:44.800
No disrespecting her, Mr. Kaieda.

01:00:44.800 --> 01:00:47.140
Look at you two lovebirds go.

01:00:47.140 --> 01:00:50.810
And here I almost had a chance with you gone.

01:00:50.810 --> 01:00:53.050
No, you did not, sir.

01:00:53.050 --> 01:00:55.020
She got you there.

01:00:55.760 --> 01:00:58.590
Hello there, folks.

01:00:58.590 --> 01:00:59.650
Evening, sir.

01:00:59.650 --> 01:01:03.300
Kikuchi, here's something
for Kaede's birthday next week.

01:01:03.300 --> 01:01:04.990
Thank you, sir. I'm honored.

01:01:04.990 --> 01:01:07.430
And Tamana, your son. Yamato, was it?

01:01:07.430 --> 01:01:09.550
- Yes, sir.
- He'll be entering middle school, right?

01:01:09.550 --> 01:01:13.020
Here's a charm
to wish him luck in his studies.

01:01:13.020 --> 01:01:16.320
- I appreciate your thoughtfulness, sir.
- Thank you.

01:01:47.260 --> 01:01:51.840
Gido, it's an honor to have you back.

01:01:51.840 --> 01:01:54.750
I'll make you your favorite, garlic rice.

01:01:54.750 --> 01:01:57.460
Much appreciated, sir.

01:01:58.110 --> 01:02:00.740
We were all worried about you, you know?

01:02:00.740 --> 01:02:05.840
Though there's plenty I want to ask,
we have one matter to address first.

01:02:06.670 --> 01:02:15.020
On April 7th, a total of 14.9 million yen
was withdrawn from two bank accounts.

01:02:16.540 --> 01:02:19.640
Here's the difficult thing about our business.

01:02:19.640 --> 01:02:23.710
We open multiple bank accounts
to keep the authorities off our tails.

01:02:23.710 --> 01:02:27.740
But then, we also lose track of the money.

01:02:27.740 --> 01:02:30.070
A small amount taken out
usually goes unnoticed.

01:02:30.070 --> 01:02:35.720
Or so you think.
But our accountants catch everything.

01:02:39.540 --> 01:02:41.950
Eat up while it's hot.

01:02:41.950 --> 01:02:44.690
- Thank you, sir.
- Thank you.

01:02:52.400 --> 01:02:54.220
Ando.

01:02:54.220 --> 01:02:57.710
You should never waste great food, no?

01:02:57.710 --> 01:03:01.280
Sir, I've never touched the money -

01:03:42.200 --> 01:03:45.960
Fuyuhashi, eat his share.
He had leftovers.

01:03:45.960 --> 01:03:48.070
Thank you, sir.

01:03:52.410 --> 01:03:55.110
I see you still have awful table manners.

01:03:55.110 --> 01:03:57.920
You should really fix that while you can.

01:03:57.920 --> 01:03:59.540
The food's good, sir.

01:03:59.540 --> 01:04:02.200
Glad to hear it. Now eat up.

01:04:03.130 --> 01:04:06.660
Excuse me. The restroom calls.

01:04:33.270 --> 01:04:37.490
I can't keep up with this.

01:05:19.520 --> 01:05:21.790
I can't give up.

01:05:21.790 --> 01:05:24.770
I have to find the culprit.

01:05:24.770 --> 01:05:27.410
You promised Takumi you'd come home.

01:05:36.950 --> 01:05:40.090
Hayase's are known for being tenacious.

01:05:56.670 --> 01:05:58.540
Now then, let's get down to business.

01:05:59.980 --> 01:06:03.850
The missing 1 billion yen remains at large, sir.

01:06:03.850 --> 01:06:07.920
You managed to track the whereabouts
of millions of yen.

01:06:07.920 --> 01:06:11.560
So how does a billion yen
slip right under your nose?

01:06:11.560 --> 01:06:15.790
Managing assets in a bank
are of no difficulty for me.

01:06:15.790 --> 01:06:20.690
But there are limits to what I can track
when it comes to cold, hard cash.

01:06:22.090 --> 01:06:28.570
Gido, I had you looking into this,
when you suddenly disappeared on us.

01:06:28.570 --> 01:06:32.130
Honestly, I suspected you first.

01:06:32.130 --> 01:06:36.180
We were searching everywhere for you.

01:06:36.180 --> 01:06:39.050
And now you've come crawling back to us.

01:06:44.580 --> 01:06:50.020
It can't be. Did she trick me?

01:06:54.830 --> 01:06:56.650
Eat up while it's hot.

01:06:56.650 --> 01:06:58.860
- Thank you.
- Thank you, sir.

01:07:02.800 --> 01:07:07.180
You should never waste great food, no?

01:07:07.180 --> 01:07:11.550
Sir, there has to be a mistake.
I never stole -

01:07:24.330 --> 01:07:27.020
Looks like I'll get another shot after all!

01:07:53.160 --> 01:07:55.580
Thank you.

01:07:55.580 --> 01:07:56.780
Nice work, Dad.

01:07:56.780 --> 01:07:58.060
Just don't tell your grandma.

01:07:58.060 --> 01:08:00.460
I'm sorry.

01:08:00.460 --> 01:08:02.980
I promise I'll come back home to you.